  <section id="intro">
    <h2>&#128269; Introduction</h2>
    <p>Artificial Intelligence (AI) is the science of creating machines that can think, learn, and make decisions. It began as a philosophical question about human thought and evolved into one of the greatest technological revolutions in history.</p>
    <div>
    <!-- Req #2: Aside Element -->
        <aside class="col-md-4" style="background-color: #1f2833; padding: 15px; border-radius: 10px;">
            <h3>Did you know?</h3>
            <p>The first AI program was written in 1951 by Christopher Strachey.</p>
        </aside>

    </div>
  </section>

  

  <section id="origins">
    <h2>&#128220; Early Origins</h2>
    <article>
      <h3>1950 &mdash; The Turing Test</h3>
      <p>Alan Turing proposed a test to measure a machine’s ability to exhibit intelligent behavior. This marked the birth of AI as an idea.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>1956 &mdash; The Dartmouth Conference</h3>
      <p>John McCarthy coined the term “Artificial Intelligence” at a summer research workshop &mdash; officially launching the field.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section id="eras">
    <h2>&#9881; The Eras of AI</h2>

    <article>
      <h3>&#129504; 1970s &mdash; Knowledge and Logic</h3>
      <p>Scientists built systems that could make logical deductions, marking the rise of “Expert Systems.”</p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h3>&#128161; 1990s &mdash; Data and Learning</h3>
      <p>With more data and faster computers, AI systems started to learn patterns using machine learning algorithms.</p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <h3>&#128640; 2010s &mdash; Deep Learning Revolution</h3>
      <p>Neural networks became powerful enough to recognize faces, understand speech, and even drive cars.</p>
    </article>
  </section>
